      <span class="tag">AI Coding</span>
      <h1>Cursor vs Windsurf: Best AI IDE for Developers in 2026</h1>
      <p class="meta">Updated June 9, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <p class="lead">
      The battle for the best AI-powered IDE is heating up in 2026, and two contenders have emerged as the definitive choices for developers who want genuine AI intelligence built into their coding environment: <strong>Cursor</strong> from Anysphere and <strong>Windsurf</strong> from Codeium. Both are AI-native code editors that go far beyond simple autocomplete, offering multi-file editing, codebase-aware chat, intelligent debugging, and natural language-driven development. But they take distinctly different approaches to how AI should integrate into the developer experience. After months of using both tools across production projects, open-source contributions, and prototype development, here is the honest, detailed comparison you need to pick the right AI IDE for your workflow.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-top">
      <a href="https://cursor.sh" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank">Try Cursor Free →</a>
      <a href="https://codeium.com/windsurf" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank">Try Windsurf Free →</a>
    </div>

    <h2>Feature Comparison Table</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Cursor</th><th>Windsurf</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Base Editor</td><td>VS Code fork</td><td>VS Code fork (Continue-based)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AI Model Options</td><th>Claude 3.5, GPT-4o, custom</th><th>GPT-4o, Claude 3.5, others</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-File Editing</td><th>Composer</th><th>Cascade</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Codebase Indexing</td><th>Full project index</th><th>Full project index</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Tab Autocomplete</th><th>Excellent (< 200ms)</th><th>Very Good (~300ms)</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Chat with Context</th><th>Yes (Cmd+K)</th><th>Yes (Ctrl+Shift+L)</th></tr>
